Citation.sAbstract: This paper reports the experimental data of densities and viscosities at six temperatures  (298.15 to 343.15) K, refractive indices at nine temperatures (293.15 to 333.15) K, and surface  tensions at seven temperatures (298.15 to 333.15) K for aqueous solutions of N, ndimethylpropanolamine  (DMPA). Excess properties derived from the experimental results were  discussed in terms of changes in molecular interactions in the mixtures. The derived deviations of the  properties were regressed with the Redlich-Kister equation. The derived thermodynamic properties  were also compared with those of other tertiary amines available in the literature.
Citation.sTitle: Volumetric Properties, Viscosities, Refractive Indices and Surface Tensions for Aqueous N, ndimethylpropanolamine  (DMPA) Solutions From 298.15 K to 343.15 K
